
[1]disciplinary

   DISCIPLINARY, a.

   1. Pertaining to discipline; intended for discipline or government;
   promoting discipline; as, certain canons of the church are
   disciplinary.

   2. Relating to a regular course of education; intended for instruction.

   The evils of life, pain, sickness, losses, sorrows, dangers and
   disappointments, are disciplinary and remedial.
